item.title: Need Help with compile+jdk!
item.dc:creator: @lothy Lothy
item.description:
@lothy wrote:

Any JDK will make the compiler work. If you don’t have the JDK, there’s a link in my sig. If you’ve set the compiler up right, then there’s no way it won’t compile the new stuff in your client class - So you’ve either: a) Set your classpath wrong. b) Haven’t got the right directory in your compiler if you haven’t set the classpath or c) You’re getting errors and because of this the compiler won’t compile the code.
